(1.2 Chosen Structures and Methods) Tj
0 -14 Td
/F1 10.5 Tf
(- **Exact lookup by ID**) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Baseline: linear scan over list.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Improved: hash index \(dict[int, record]\).) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Reason: hash table gives expected O\(1\) query time after one O\(n\) build.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- **Frequency counting**) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Used collections.Counter on a categorical field \(category or region\).) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Reason: direct and efficient one-pass counting.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- **Duplicate detection**) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Rule used: duplicate \(name, year\).) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Structure: defaultdict\(list\) grouping by \(name, year\).) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Reason: grouping by key is simple and linear-time.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- **Top-k by score**) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Method A: full sort by score descending.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Method B: heapq.nlargest\(k, ...\).) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Reason: sorting is straightforward baseline, heap is asymptotically better) Tj
0 -14 Td
(for small k.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- **Range query on numeric field \(value\)**) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Method A: linear filtering.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Method B: sort once + binary search with bisect_left/bisect_right.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  - Reason: preprocessing cost can be amortized over repeated queries.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
